modules.description: Handles input validation by ensuring all opened brackets are properly closed before accepting user input. Works with string-based user input and maintains a history of commands for navigation. Useful for building interactive programming language environments where syntax correctness is critical during input.

Reads user input with customizable prompt, delimiter, and bracket matching, returning the input string upon encountering a newline or specified delimiter. Handles command history, tab completion, and hints during input. Operates on strings, characters, and custom callback functions for interactive command-line interfaces.
